	<text>
		<body>
			<div type="entry">
				<pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary57.jpg"/>
				<head><date>Monday 7.</date></head>
				<p>It was <name key="Positive" type="Weather">bright fine summer morning</name> but
						<name key="Negetive" type="Weather">commenced raining</name> about
						<time>twelve o'clock</time>, &amp; <name key="Negetive" type="Weather"
						>rained</name>
					<time>until evening</time>. We had a regimental roll call, &amp; company drill.
					I spent most of the day writing <objectName key="Readable">letters</objectName>
					to <persName key="John Blair Linn" role="Brother" cert="high"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper051"
						type="real">John</persName> &amp; <persName key="Louisa">Louisa</persName>
					&amp; one to <persName role="Jim Kelly's wife">Jim Kelly's wife</persName>. This
					evening <persName key="Jacob G. Beaver" role="Soldier" cert="high"
						ref="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/BucknellDSC/jmlinn/refs/heads/main/jmlinn_personography.xml#jmlper003"
						type="real">Beaver</persName> and I shot <placeName role="Town center">down
						town</placeName>. It was very desolate. The [sandy]? evil drinks in the rain
					as fast as it falls. It looked odd to see the <name key="Negetive"
						type="Weather">rain come pouring down</name>, &amp; sort of melt away like
